org.svvrl.goal.core.comp.schewe
Class Node

java.lang.Object
  org.svvrl.goal.core.comp.schewe.Node
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable

A Node is a tree node in a history tree. Every node has two IDs, namely CID and UID. CID is unique in the siblings while UID is unique in the tree. The CID is used to determine older siblings. If a sibling has a smaller CID than this node, then the sibling is older. The equality of nodes is determined only by their UIDs.

Author:
Ming-Hsien Tsai
